  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="NA86-kiḷavi">itu kuṟittap paruvattiṉ viṉaimuṭittu vantamai kēṭṭa tōḻi talaivik kuraittatu.</p>
        <p xml:lang="en">This is what the confidante, who had heard of [his] return after the work had been finished at the time he intended, said to HER.</p>
      </div>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <lg xml:id="NA86">
<l>            aṟavar vāḻi tōḻi maṟavar</l>
<l>            vēleṉa virinta katuppiṟ ṟōla</l>
<l>            pāṇṭi loppiṟ pakaṉṟai malaruṅ</l>
<l>            kaṭumpaṉi yaṟcira naṭuṅkak kāṇṭakak</l>
<l>            kaival viṉaivaṉ ṟaiyupu corinta </l>
<l>            curitaka vuruviṉa vākip periya</l>
<l>            kōṅkaṅ kuvimukai yaviḻa vīṅkai</l>
<l>            naṟṟaḷir nayavara nuṭaṅku</l>
<l>            muṟṟā vēṉiṉ muṉṉivan tōrē.</l>
        </lg>
       <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>Dutiful [is] he<note place="foot">Here we might also read a general statement, and then the construction has to be understood in a different way, namely <term xml:lang="ta">aṟavar</term> as an ante-positioned predicate noun and <term xml:lang="ta">vantōr</term> as subject: "dutiful [are] those who have come back before summer is at an end". The implication is in any case that HE has not come back in time, since SHE is shivering in the dew.</note>, oh friend,</l>
<l>– who has come back before summer is at an end,</l>
<l rend="indent">when the good sprouts of the mimosa are swaying so as to raise</l>
<l rend="indent3">longing,</l>
<l rend="indent2">while the piled buds of the Kōṅkam are opening,</l>
<l rend="indent3">the big ones having the form of hair-ornaments,</l>
<l rend="indent3">cast [and] inlaid by a craftsman skilful with [his] hands</l>
<l rend="indent4">in a way fit to be seen,</l>
<l rend="indent2">while [we] are shivering in the cold season with harsh dew,</l>
<l rend="indent3">when the Pakaṉṟai blossoms, resembling disks</l>
<l rend="indent4">of hairy hide spread like spears(?)<note place="foot">What can be the point of <term xml:lang="ta">vēl eṉa</term> here? Can anything look like a disk and a spear at the same time?</note> by the bold ones.</l>
        </lg>
         </div>
